[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ipswich Town: David McGoldrick and Luke Hyam face lengthy lay-offs

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Ipswich Town's David McGoldrick and Luke Hyam are both set to miss lengthy periods through injury.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Manager Mick McCarthy confirmed striker McGoldrick, 28, will not need surgery but will be sidelined for eight to 10 weeks with an ankle ligament injury.
Midfielder Hyam, 24, is set to miss up to a month with a knee injury.
The Tractor Boys will also be without striker Brett Pitman, 28 and 21-year-old Everton-loanee Conor Grant when they face Wolves on Tuesday.
